      "content": "The interpretation of the Second Amendment is a matter of deep legal and philosophical debate, and both sides present compelling arguments. Those who argue the current Supreme Court is adhering to the Founders' intent often point to the text and historical understanding of the right to bear arms for self-defense. Conversely, critics argue that modern rulings reflect an expansive view that goes beyond the original understanding of militia service. Ultimately, the \"legally sound\" side depends on which constitutional theory—originalism or living constitutionalism—you adopt.",
